============================================================
PHASE 14 OBJECTIVE
============================================================

Build the native desktop, partner distribution, and public launch layer for zDash.

Main goals:

1. Add Tauri desktop app shell
2. Package zDash as a secure native desktop control panel
3. Add desktop login/session flow
4. Add desktop tray status monitor
5. Add desktop local agent bridge
6. Add offline-readonly mode
7. Add desktop auto-update shell
8. Add installer build scripts for Windows/macOS/Linux
9. Add partner marketplace publishing workflow
10. Add plugin/package distribution pipeline
11. Add public cloud launch landing system
12. Add public waitlist and invite system
13. Add launch readiness checklist
14. Add public status page shell
15. Add product telemetry with privacy controls
16. Add release notes and changelog automation
17. Add package signing placeholders
18. Add public documentation publishing scripts
19. Add enterprise deployment bundle generator
20. Add final launch tests and acceptance gates

IMPORTANT SAFETY RULES:
- Do not enable live trading by default.
- Do not enable real IoT actions by default.
- Do not enable real social posting by default.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass content approval checks.
- Do not bypass tenant isolation.
- Do not bypass billing entitlements.
- Do not bypass governance policies.
- Do not expose secrets in desktop, frontend, mobile, logs, telemetry, installers, exports, docs, or marketplace metadata.
- Desktop app must never store raw API keys or raw passwords.
- Desktop local bridge must be disabled by default.
- Marketplace publishing must require security review.
- Public launch flows must default to sandbox/demo mode.
- Telemetry must be opt-in or privacy-safe.
- Installer scripts must fail safely.
- Update system must verify signatures when real signing is configured.

