============================================================
IMPORTANT IMPLEMENTATION RULES
============================================================

- Do not use pseudocode.
- Do not skip files.
- Do not remove Phase 1–13 behavior.
- Keep all existing backend tests passing.
- Keep all existing frontend tests passing.
- Use typed Python where reasonable.
- Use TypeScript types.
- Use safe Rust patterns for Tauri commands.
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.x style.
- Never hardcode secrets.
- Never expose secrets in frontend, mobile, desktop, logs, telemetry, installers, docs, or bundles.
- Never log tokens.
- Never store raw invite codes.
- Never store raw signing keys.
- Never enable live trading by default.
- Never enable real social posting by default.
- Never enable real IoT power actions by default.
- Never bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Never bypass content approval checks.
- Never bypass tenant isolation.
- Never bypass billing entitlements.
- Never bypass governance policies.
- Keep desktop local bridge disabled and dry-run by default.
- Keep marketplace publishing security-review-gated.
- Keep public launch sandbox/demo-first.
- Keep telemetry privacy-safe.
- Keep code modular enough for Phase 15 AI marketplace expansion, enterprise partner launch, and production GA.

